d; cite a foundational study (e.g., Forer, 1949) to reinforce the explanation.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": null}, {"id": "5ce95e7b-2a8a-427f-b006-862226aee9f8", "versionId": "59279870-1587-427d-a2a1-21c37bd53aa8", "criterionId": null, "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 2, "bbox": {"x": 0.0869, "y": 0.5027, "width": 0.8401000000000001, "height": 0.06409999999999993}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.0869, "y": 0.5027}, {"x": 0.927, "y": 0.5027}, {"x": 0.927, "y": 0.5668}, {"x": 0.0869, "y": 0.5668}], "comment": "The statement that the algorithm \u00e2\u0080\u009cremoves\u00e2\u0080\u009d human bias overlooks the bias inherent in training data; discuss data-sampling bias explicitly.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": null}, {"id": "cfae197b-d06a-4c8b-b9a2-4ca8908be186", "versionId": "59279870-1587-427d-a2a1-21c37bd53aa8", "criterionId": null, "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 2, "bbox": {"x": 0.0869, "y": 0.5828, "width": 0.8401000000000001, "height": 0.09620000000000006}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.0869, "y": 0.5828}, {"x": 0.927, "y": 0.5828}, {"x": 0.927, "y": 0.679}, {"x": 0.0869, "y": 0.679}], "comment": "The disparity rates in false positives/negatives are critical; analyse why these arise (e.g., feature selection, historical crime data) to deepen TOK insight.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": null}, {"id": "2e918a3a-2237-446c-a22c-4d6a3e3b5946", "versionId": "59279870-1587-427d-a2a1-21c37bd53aa8", "criterionId": null, "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 2, "bbox": {"x": 0.0869, "y": 0.6937, "width": 0.8401000000000001, "height": 0.12819999999999998}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.0869, "y": 0.6937}, {"x": 0.927, "y": 0.6937}, {"x": 0.927, "y": 0.8219}, {"x": 0.0869, "y": 0.8219}], "comment": "Attributing machine-learning bias to confirmation